00084 afx_msg LRESULT CGpiTransferProgressDlg::OnGpiTransferStateChange( WPARAM, LPARAM )
00085 {
00086     switch ( mCom.mGpiTransferState )
00087     {
00088     //set mTransferStatus
00089     case FmiApplicationLayer::TRANSFER_NOT_STARTED:
00090         GetDlgItem( IDOK )->EnableWindow( TRUE );
00091         mTransferStatus.Format( _T("No Transfer") );
00092         break;
00093     case FmiApplicationLayer::TRANSFER_STARTED:
00094         GetDlgItem( IDOK )->EnableWindow( FALSE );
00095         mTransferStatus.Format( _T("Starting Transfer") );
00096         break;
00097     case FmiApplicationLayer::TRANSFER_IN_PROGRESS:
00098         GetDlgItem( IDOK )->EnableWindow( FALSE );
00099         mProgressBar.SetRange32( 0, mCom.mGpiFileTransferSize );
00100         mProgressBar.SetPos( 0 );
00101         break;
00102     case FmiApplicationLayer::TRANSFER_COMPLETED:
00103         GetDlgItem( IDOK )->EnableWindow( TRUE );
00104         GetDlgItem( IDC_GPIPROGRESS_BTN_STOP )->EnableWindow( FALSE );
00105         mTransferStatus.Format( _T("Done") );
00106         break;
00107     case FmiApplicationLayer::TRANSFER_FAILED:
00108         GetDlgItem( IDOK )->EnableWindow( TRUE );
00109         GetDlgItem( IDC_GPIPROGRESS_BTN_STOP )->EnableWindow( FALSE );
00110         if( mStopButtonClicked )
00111             mTransferStatus.Format( _T("Canceled at user request") );
00112         else
00113             mTransferStatus.Format( _T("Failed") );
00114         break;
00115     default:
00116         break;
00117     }
00118     UpdateData( FALSE );
00119     return 0;
00120 }
